<br>
1. You talk about a guild rejoining a list, but don't address an alliance.  Personally, I'd make them post the 18 again, but it's up to you.<br>
<br>
2. You have listed guilds which will not be allowed on the list due to perceived levels of membership.  You may wish to state under what conditions you will be removing guilds, in the future, who can currently fight Vox/Naggy, and how they might appeal it.<br>
<br>
3. I've never run a message board before, but requiring a small guild to create one might be a little excessive.  If I ran a small guild of under 20 members and planned to keep it small, I'd mostly just handle issues in-game and through emails; but that's just my style.  Plus, having a board can mean very little.  Someone could throw one up quick and have it just be a front.<br>
<br>
I'd suggest that if you see a guild tag in game, that should be enough.  If Verant can recognize it as a guild, don't see why the reservation system can't.  Not sure what you are trying to prevent with this limitation.<br>
<br>
Everything else looks good.  Nice job.<br>
<br>
