</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrungleeisenguss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krungle Eisenguss</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Hero of Kaladim</span><br>  Posts: 733<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 4:37:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Vox/Nagafen rules posted and effective immediately.</span><hr size=1> Mmm...I have something to say about the &quot;primary charactor&quot; thing.<br>
<br>
Let's say you have an alt that is the right level to kill an old world dragon. You play that alt alot as you also play your main. Why should your alt not be allowed to do its thing independently of the main?<br>
<br>
A real for instance ( not to mention names ) is a mid 50's Necro in one guild with a low 50's ( dragon level ) Paladin Alt in another guild. I think the Paladin should be counted toward the 18.<br>
<br>
Also there are alot of guilds that are bringing up alts as their mains reach the upper 50's. Why should these alts be penalized in their chances at early Dragon loot with their guilds?<br>
<br>
With Naggy all you NEED is 4 groups and with Vox 5. Recommended is one more group for each. By forcing the up and coming Alts out and forcing the equivilent of 18 early non-duplicate sign-ups for each raid, aren't you hurting the chances of Indies, Alts and Power Dragon Raiders ( like me ) from being able to be involved in Old World Dragon Raids?<br>
<br>
To say to me &quot;just level up and do Gore&quot; is trying to tell me how to play the game. That is just wrong. I feel I have a better chance at a Vox Book than I would have at a Gore book, both because of the orginization of Vox reservations and the drop rates of the book between the two dragons.<br>
<br>
Note: These are my personal opinions and not that of my guild or guild leadership.<br>
<br>
Krungle<br>
